Package: multixoR
Title: Five-Dimensional Multiverse Tic-Tac-Toe
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Raban",
           family = "Heller",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "raban.heller@charite.de",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8006-9742"))
Description: A five-dimensional, multiverse variant of tic-tac-toe. Two
    players, 'X' and 'O', place marks on a four-by-four-by-four spatial
    cube. Beyond the three spatial axes, play extends across a time axis
    (successive board states) and a timeline axis (parallel, branching
    universes). A player wins by completing a straight line of three marks
    of their own colour along any axis or diagonal, including lines that
    run through time and across timelines. The engine implements generic
    'n^d' lattice geometry, single-placement plies, history-immutable
    branching into the past, and incremental cross-axis win detection.
